The paper deals with lattice reduction, which is a common technique used in information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) for solving problems related to MIMO detection. The paper also discusses a new framework called sequential reduction, which can be seen as a data structure problem (cs.DS) and involves the use of hash-based algorithms (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents simulation results that compare the performance of different reduction algorithms, which can be seen as a machine learning problem (cs.LG).
